values:
Actually, the first thing she said was &quot;You're joking right?&quot;

Ah well, at least I didn't have to tackle her into the surf.&nbsp; I would have hated to find the ring in the sand in the moonlight...

I'm so fucking happy right now... and Carrie can't stop spazzing over it all.&nbsp; We have no clue where or when we'll be having the ceremony, but we'll figure it out!


BTW we went to Hilton Head for the occasion, which was really fun, although a word of warning: They charge you there just to get on to the island.&nbsp;

Greetings all!&nbsp; This is the first post in this journal, Carrie finally seduced me over to the dark side of LJness.&nbsp; So now I, like many, many before me, shall proceed to flood the internets with the mediocre drivel which in some shape or form represents my life until such a time that I either forget my own password or die due to an overdose of caffeine.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

So, where to start. 

Spring break is whizzing by faster than a meth-powered freight train, but in spite of it's hasty pace I'm pleased to say I'm thoroughly enjoying sitting on my ass doing diddly-squat for once.&nbsp; Last quarter was one helluva ride, between Senior Project 2, Interactive Production, Independent Study, and Art History 3 with Kessenich, the sweetest sadist I have ever met.&nbsp; Towards the end getting two square meals (in this context meaning it comes from a square box delivered to our front door by some poor shmuck)&nbsp; and 3 hours a sleep in a 24 hour period was the equivalent of winning the jackpot.&nbsp; But now that it's over, I've turned my attentions to other things, like eating things which quite frankly probably truncate my lifespan considerably, sleeping until 2 in the afternoon, surfing the bowels of the internets with Carrie as my co-pilot, revitalizing my FurAffinity account, and waiting for the two guys I did a medical animation for to get around to paying me.

I've decided to take a sabbatical from the Kamikaze project during this break to focus on developing another series I've been toying with for a while.&nbsp; I've had an idea for a pulp-scifi Mike Mignola-meets-David Weber style graphic novel (read web comic)&nbsp; featuring two anthro dragons in space.&nbsp; Another way to look at it would be to take the movie Domino, give it a plot transplant, and then change the&nbsp; setting, the characters, and then make it a comic that for all intents-and-purposes is one huge fucking speed-painting.&nbsp; Needles to say there is still a lot of concept work to be done, but I'm hoping to have a prototype story printed and ready for test sales at RCFM.&nbsp; Given that this year's theme is sci-fi, I'm hoping it will do well.&nbsp; I'll be posting concept art on FA, and possible dA as well as things progress.&nbsp; 

Hmmm, I guess that's enough damage for a first post.&nbsp; I'll leave it at that for now.
